title: SpaceX to take over West Coast launch pad previously used by ULA
summary: SpaceX is getting a second launch pad on the West Coast after gaining approval to lease Space Launch Complex 6 (SLC-6) at Vandenberg Space Force Base, California, a historic pad previously occupied by United Launch Alliance.

title: NASA Selects 12 Companies to Collaborate on Key Technology Development
summary: NASA has selected 16 proposals from 12 companies under the 2022 Announcement of Collaboration Opportunity (ACO) to advance capabilities and technologies related to NASA's Moon to Mars Objectives. title: Ursa Major Engine To Be Used On Astra Rocket 4
summary: Ursa Major CEO, Joe Laurienti, says that the partnership with Astra “marks an important industry milestone in outsourcing propulsion to unlock growth and innovation for launch providers”

title: First ispace lunar lander feared lost
summary: Controllers lost contact with a lunar lander developed by a Japanese company moments before its scheduled touchdown, raising fears the spacecraft crashed during its final descent.

title: NASA Retires Mineral Mapping Instrument on Mars Orbiter
summary: One of six instruments aboard the agency’s Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter, CRISM produced global maps of minerals on the Red Planet’s surface.
